## 1. Problem Statement

The firm has a EUR-denominated receivable of €12,500,000 due in one year from a European client engagement. At the current spot rate of 1.0875 USD/EUR, the exposure is approximately $13.59 million. This creates material foreign exchange (FX) risk, as fluctuations in the EUR/USD exchange rate will directly impact USD cash flows.

A depreciation of the euro would reduce the USD value of the receivable, potentially resulting in a significant revenue shortfall. For example, a 5–10% decline in EUR/USD could reduce proceeds by over $600,000 to $1.2 million. The objective of this model is to evaluate hedging strategies that mitigate downside risk while considering cost and upside participation.

---

## 2. Inputs (Known Variables)

| Named Range | Description | Unit | Value | Source |
|------------|------------|------|------|--------|
| FC_AMT | Foreign-currency receivable | EUR | 12,500,000 | Stage 1 Memo |
| S0_in | Spot rate at inception | USD/EUR | 1.0875 | Bloomberg |
| F0_in | Forward rate (1-year) | USD/EUR | 1.0910 | Given |
| R_USD | USD interest rate | % annual | 3.33% | Assumed |
| R_FC | EUR interest rate | % annual | 3.00% | Assumed |
| K_PUT | Put option strike | USD/EUR | 1.0875 | Assumed |
| K_CALL | Call option strike | USD/EUR | 1.1000 | Assumed |
| PREM_PUT | Put premium per EUR | USD | 0.017 | Given |
| PREM_CALL | Call premium per EUR | USD | 0.022 | Given |
| T_DAYS | Time to settlement | Days | 360 | Assumed |

---

## 3. Assumptions & Constraints

- Interest rates are simple annual rates using a 360-day convention.
- No transaction costs, taxes, or bid-ask spreads.
- Options are European-style.
- Forward and money market hedges satisfy parity.
- Premiums are paid upfront.
- No credit or counterparty risk.
- Deterministic sensitivity (no stochastic modeling).

---

## 4. Calculation Flow

### 4.1 Forward Hedge
USD proceeds = FC_AMT × F0_in

### 4.2 Money Market Hedge
1. Discount EUR receivable
2. Convert to USD at spot
3. Invest at USD rate

### 4.3 Protective Put
USD proceeds = FC_AMT × max(K_PUT, S_T) − premium

### 4.4 Risk Reversal
USD proceeds = FC_AMT × min(max(S_T, K_PUT), K_CALL) − net premium

